yearLabel.formatter.desc:
Formatter of year text label, which supports string template and callback function. By default, the current range of the year, if the interval across the year, showing the first year and the last year Examples: 

   // Use string template; eg: ['2017-10-11', '2018-01-21']
   /*
       template variables:
       {nameMap} default nameMap eg：'2017-2018'
       {start}   start year eg: 2017
       {end}   end year eg: 2018
   */

   formatter: '{start}-{end}'

   // Use callback function;
   /*
       function parameters:
       param.nameMap default nameMap eg：'2017-2018'
       param.start   start year eg: 2017
       param.end   end year eg: 2018
   */
   formatter: function (param) {
       // ...
       return param.end;
   }

